Package com.vmware.esx.settings.clusters.software.drafts.software

The com.vmware.esx.settings.clusters.software.drafts.software package provides interfaces to manage draft of the software documents for ESX cluster.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AddOn
    The AddOn interface provides methods to manage the OEM add-on specification in a software draft.
    AddOn.DeleteInvocation
    Invocable that represents the AddOn#delete vAPI operation.
    AddOn.GetInvocation
    Invocable that represents the AddOn#get vAPI operation.
    AddOn.SetInvocation
    Invocable that represents the AddOn#set vAPI operation.
    AddOnTypes
    Defines the data types of the AddOn API service.
    BaseImage
    The BaseImage interface provides methods to manage the base-image specification in a software draft.
    BaseImage.GetInvocation
    Invocable that represents the BaseImage#get vAPI operation.
    BaseImage.SetInvocation
    Invocable that represents the BaseImage#set vAPI operation.
    BaseImageTypes
    Defines the data types of the BaseImage API service.
    Components
    The Components interface provides methods to manage component specification in a software draft.
    Components.DeleteInvocation
    Invocable that represents the Components#delete vAPI operation.
    Components.GetInvocation
    Invocable that represents the Components#get vAPI operation.
    Components.ListInvocation
    Invocable that represents the Components#list vAPI operation.
    Components.SetInvocation
    Invocable that represents the Components#set vAPI operation.
    Components.UpdateInvocation
    Invocable that represents the Components#update vAPI operation.
    ComponentsTypes
    Defines the data types of the Components API service.
    EffectiveComponents
    The EffectiveComponents interface provides methods to manage effective list of components.
    EffectiveComponents.ListInvocation
    Invocable that represents the EffectiveComponents#list vAPI operation.
    EffectiveComponentsTypes
    Defines the data types of the EffectiveComponents API service.
    HardwareSupport
    The HardwareSupport interface provides methods to manage a cluster's Hardware Support Package (HSP) configuration in working copy documents.
    HardwareSupport.DeleteInvocation
    Invocable that represents the HardwareSupport#delete vAPI operation.
    HardwareSupport.GetInvocation
    Invocable that represents the HardwareSupport#get vAPI operation.
    HardwareSupport.SetInvocation
    Invocable that represents the HardwareSupport#set vAPI operation.
    HardwareSupportTypes
    Defines the data types of the HardwareSupport API service.

Package com.vmware.esx.settings.clusters.software.drafts.software Description

The com.vmware.esx.settings.clusters.software.drafts.software package provides interfaces to manage draft of the software documents for ESX cluster.
